<b>Behold the power of Pink Capri's!</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ragefire is my pet</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/02 10:58:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=791.topic&index=708>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Ragefire Rotation List</span><hr size=1> List finally updated, including people joining list since 1/3.<br>
<br>
Currently, Medious is in limbo pending a resolution to the latest issue, putting Kealoha up. This limbo will last untill late sunday night/monday morning. The Medious situation is a new one for us, which I am surprised about. I half-expected to run into this problem already long ago, but thankfully we haven't.<br>
<br>
Currently, there are no official procedures written down anywhere for involuntarily removing someone from the list for failure to camp Ragefire. Currently, the list holder pretty much lets everyone know what's happening, then lays down a decision, hoping a major revolt doesnt come of it. That's worked fine till now, but at this point, more structure is needed. Obviously, this issue is very rare (happened... maybe once?) The list-holder needs to have flexibility and discretion of the issues, but on the other hand, the clerics on the list need more clarification on this issue, this time, and in the future. Plus, there needs to be a more democratic approach in case the list-holder ever wanted to do one thing, and the vast majority of the list wants to overrule to do another thing, or even if the list clerics decide they want a new list-holder. I dont expect &quot;votes&quot; to be necessary like this very often, at all. Maybe once a month at the most, if even that. The only other time the list-holder has had a vote of any kind, was when there was a large objection to the no-switching rule. (unofficial vote showed me that most of the list appeared to agree with me, so the change stood.)<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm gonna wing it a little on Medious, and try to post a more permenant clarification for the future. Details to be posted on the front page soon, let me know what you think! Now, for Medious. I would not have brought this up as an issue myself, if left just up to me. However, almost half a dozen clerics have now complained, and so we've got to take a look at it. <br>
<br>
He is currently in #2 limbo untill Sunday night. Our options here are very simple. Let him have another chance after whoever is on top sunday night is finished, or drop him to the bottom. Myself, I do not agree with bumping Medious, just yet. I'm inclined to let him have another chance, because there are clerics in the past who missed even more camps than Medious had, but I cant ignore the possibility that most of the list might disagree with me. So, from tonight through sunday eve, I will poll the current list clerics (on list as of tonight) for their opinions. (Yes, no, I dont care) I'll repost this issue in a seperate topic as well for more visibility. List clerics can either tell me online, or post their opinion in that topic only if their board-name is well-known. (not a newbie account out of the blue). Names will be listed along with how they &quot;voted.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is serious to me, I dont want a simple majority, I'll want a super-majority of 2/3 saying &quot;do it&quot; to go ahead with the repeatedly posted request to drop Medious to the bottom. If we fall short of 2/3 on sunday night, then Medious comes out of limbo as #2 on the list, behind whoever is #1 at that time. <br>
<br>
(This would need 2/3 of those who actually give a vote of some kind. &quot;Not sure/dont know/dont care&quot; would be a valid vote, and would pretty much act like a no vote, and not a yes. non-votes are treated like they didnt exist when sunday night rolls around) <p>Cayleu Starshine
