<br>
Cayleu - Keep the list and rules as simple as possible.  Your new process for changinig rules is well thought out, but may be too complicated.  If things get too complicated, people will just start saying they don't understand, etc... and ignoring the list.  Personally, I would just say &quot;I'll make judgements about removing or bumping people down the list when need be, if you don't like it... tough @#%$&quot;.  You run the list, I think the community trusts your judgement.  And to be honest, in the end you can't make a rule or process for every decision... your judgement must be trusted for the process to work.<br>
<br>
To anyone that complains about list order, bumping people, etc. - Relax! This process has worked for a long time based on the general cooperation of the server.  It will never be perfect, some people may get treated unfairly, etc.  Life goes on... it's still better then the vicious battles everyone would be in if the list wasn't around.  <br>
<br>
